The paper deals with computational complexity and graph algorithms, which are typically covered in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of subgraphs in graphs, which falls under the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The use of the k-Sum Conjecture, which is a problem in number theory, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of graph structures such as matching, star, path, and cycle, which may be relevant to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
